This is a pretty well done doc. on the career of the lovely Sable.  I recommend this Home Video to any fan of Wrestling divas and or WWF/E.  I wish the WWE would release more dvd's on the careers of divas by themself, not all together like they do.

If I had to pick one WWE star to make it big, it would have been Sable. Nothing against the Rock (who should be the next Superman), but I'd rather look at the box of this video for two hours than see "Scorpion King."
After viewing "Sable Unleashed" with my friend chatchi, I have to say that she has the biggest charisma of any public figure I've ever seen.
She's a strong female role model -- alluring, yet self-confident. The heck with Spice Girls; Sable's got "Girl Power" in spades!
This video is more than just empty "T&A" because it gives you a sense of a woman who does whatever it takes to succeed. Hopefully, her days in the spotlight are far from over.
My only criticism of this tape is the title. "Unleashed" implies that Sable is a dog. Nothing could be further from the truth.
